## 1. Project Overview

TribeTask helps households stay organized by distributing chores fairly, allowing members to claim tasks, sending smart nudges and reminders, and gamifying participation via a leaderboard. It targets families and roommates who want a lightweight, real-time shared task management experience.

**Design Principles:**
- Mobile-first, fully responsive UI
- Accessible to all users (WCAG 2.1 AA)
- Real-time updates without page refreshes
- Fair and transparent task distribution

---

## 2. Tech Stack

| Layer | Technology | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| **Frontend Framework** | [Next.js 14+ (App Router)](https://nextjs.org) | SSR, SSG, API routes, routing |
| **Styling** | [Tailwind CSS v3](https://tailwindcss.com) | Utility-first responsive styling |
| **Backend / Database** | [Supabase](https://supabase.com) | PostgreSQL DB, Auth, Realtime, Storage |
| **Deployment** | [Vercel](https://vercel.com) | Hosting, edge functions, CI/CD previews |
| **Language** | TypeScript | Type safety across the full stack |
| **ORM / Query** | Supabase JS Client + typed queries | Database interactions |
| **State Management** | React Context + `use` hooks / Zustand (if needed) | UI state |
| **Forms** | React Hook Form + Zod | Validation and form handling |
| **Notifications** | Supabase Realtime + Web Push API | Nudges and reminders |
| **Testing** | Vitest + React Testing Library + Playwright | Unit, integration, E2E |
| **Linting** | ESLint + Prettier | Code quality and formatting |

---

## 3. Architecture

TribeTask follows a **clean, layered architecture** inside the Next.js App Router:

```
User Request
    ↓
Next.js App Router (Page / Layout components)
    ↓
Server Components / Server Actions
    ↓
Service Layer (business logic — pure functions)
    ↓
Repository Layer (Supabase data access)
    ↓
Supabase (PostgreSQL + Realtime + Auth + Storage)
```

### Layers

| Layer | Location | Responsibility |
|---|---|---|
| **UI / Pages** | `app/` | Rendering, routing, layouts |
| **Components** | `components/` | Reusable, accessible UI primitives |
| **Server Actions** | `app/**/actions.ts` | Form mutations, secure server-side ops |
| **Services** | `lib/services/` | Business logic, task distribution algorithms |
| **Repositories** | `lib/repositories/` | All Supabase queries isolated here |
| **Types** | `lib/types/` | Shared TypeScript interfaces and Zod schemas |
| **Hooks** | `hooks/` | Client-side data fetching and subscriptions |

### Key Design Rules
- **No direct Supabase calls in components** — always go through a repository or server action.
- **Server Components by default** — use `"use client"` only when interactivity requires it.
- **Row-Level Security (RLS) on all tables** — security enforced at the database layer.
- **Typed end-to-end** — generate Supabase types with `supabase gen types typescript`.

---

## 4. Core Features

### 4.1 Task Distribution (Schedule-Based)
- Households define recurring chores (daily, weekly, monthly).
- A **distribution algorithm** in `lib/services/distribution.ts` assigns tasks:
  - Round-robin among household members.
  - Weighted by member availability (optional preference settings).
  - Avoids assigning same chore to the same person consecutively.
- Scheduled via **Supabase Edge Functions** (cron) + `pg_cron` to generate task instances at the start of each period.
- Members can view their personal task queue and the full household schedule.

**Business Rules:**
- A task must always have an `assigned_to` or be in `unassigned` state.
- Recurring tasks auto-generate instances; one-off tasks are manually created.
- Tasks not completed by their due date auto-escalate to `overdue` status.

---

### 4.2 Claiming Tasks
- Members can **claim** any `unassigned` task from the shared pool.
- A task in `assigned` state can be **released** back to the pool by its owner (before due date).
- Claiming is optimistic on the UI, confirmed via Supabase Realtime.
- A task can only be claimed by one member at a time (enforced by DB constraint + RLS).

**States:** `unassigned` → `assigned` → `in_progress` → `completed` | `overdue`

---

### 4.3 Nudges
- Any household member can send a **nudge** to the person assigned to an overdue or upcoming task.
- Nudges are rate-limited: max 1 nudge per task per member per 24 hours.
- Delivered via:
  - In-app notification (Supabase Realtime `notifications` table).
  - Web Push notification (if the member has granted push permission).
- Nudges are friendly by default (preset messages) with optional custom text (max 120 chars).

---

### 4.4 Leaderboard
- A per-household **monthly leaderboard** ranks members by:
  1. Tasks completed on time (primary)
  2. Tasks completed early (tiebreaker)
  3. Streak (consecutive weeks with all tasks done)
- Scores reset on the 1st of each month (historical data preserved).
- Displayed as a ranked list with avatars, points, and badges.
- Badges awarded for milestones (e.g., "Streak King 🔥", "Early Bird 🐦", "Reliable Rockstar ⭐").

---

### 4.5 Reminders
- Automatic reminders sent at configurable intervals before a task's due date.
- Default schedule: 24 hours before, 2 hours before.
- Members configure reminder preferences per household in their profile settings.
- Delivery channels: in-app notification + email (via Supabase Auth email / Resend) + Web Push.
- Reminder jobs run via **Supabase Edge Function** on a cron schedule (every 15 min).

---

## 5. Database Schema

All tables live in the `public` schema. RLS is enabled on every table.

### 5.1 Entity Relationship Overview

```
users ──< household_members >── households
households ──< chore_templates
households ──< task_instances ──< nudges
task_instances ──< task_completions
users ──< notifications
households ──< leaderboard_entries
```

---

### 5.2 Table Definitions

```sql
-- ─────────────────────────────────────────────
-- HOUSEHOLDS
-- ─────────────────────────────────────────────
CREATE TABLE households (
  id          UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
  name        TEXT NOT NULL,
  invite_code TEXT UNIQUE NOT NULL DEFAULT substr(md5(random()::text), 1, 8),
  created_by  UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES auth.users(id) ON DELETE SET NULL,
  created_at  TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now(),
  updated_at  TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now()
);

-- ─────────────────────────────────────────────
-- HOUSEHOLD MEMBERS  (junction: user ↔ household)
-- ─────────────────────────────────────────────
CREATE TABLE household_members (
  id           UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
  household_id UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES households(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
  user_id      UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES auth.users(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
  role         TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'member' CHECK (role IN ('owner', 'admin', 'member')),
  display_name TEXT,
  avatar_url   TEXT,
  points       INT NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,
  joined_at    TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now(),
  UNIQUE (household_id, user_id)
);

-- ─────────────────────────────────────────────
-- CHORE TEMPLATES  (recurring chore definitions)
-- ─────────────────────────────────────────────
CREATE TABLE chore_templates (
  id             UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
  household_id   UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES households(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
  title          TEXT NOT NULL,
  description    TEXT,
  recurrence     TEXT NOT NULL CHECK (recurrence IN ('daily', 'weekly', 'biweekly', 'monthly', 'one_off')),
  recurrence_day INT,              -- 0=Sunday … 6=Saturday for weekly; 1-31 for monthly
  duration_mins  INT,              -- estimated effort
  points_value   INT NOT NULL DEFAULT 10,
  created_by     UUID REFERENCES auth.users(id) ON DELETE SET NULL,
  created_at     TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now(),
  updated_at     TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now(),
  is_active      BOOLEAN NOT NULL DEFAULT true
);

-- ─────────────────────────────────────────────
-- TASK INSTANCES  (generated from templates or one-off)
-- ─────────────────────────────────────────────
CREATE TABLE task_instances (
  id             UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
  household_id   UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES households(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
  template_id    UUID REFERENCES chore_templates(id) ON DELETE SET NULL,
  title          TEXT NOT NULL,
  description    TEXT,
  assigned_to    UUID REFERENCES auth.users(id) ON DELETE SET NULL,
  status         TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'unassigned'
                   CHECK (status IN ('unassigned', 'assigned', 'in_progress', 'completed', 'overdue', 'skipped')),
  due_at         TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL,
  points_value   INT NOT NULL DEFAULT 10,
  created_at     TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now(),
  updated_at     TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now()
);

-- Index for fast household task lookups
CREATE INDEX idx_task_instances_household_status ON task_instances(household_id, status);
CREATE INDEX idx_task_instances_assigned_to      ON task_instances(assigned_to);
CREATE INDEX idx_task_instances_due_at           ON task_instances(due_at);

-- ─────────────────────────────────────────────
-- TASK COMPLETIONS
-- ─────────────────────────────────────────────
CREATE TABLE task_completions (
  id              UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
  task_id         UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES task_instances(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
  completed_by    UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES auth.users(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
  completed_at    TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now(),
  photo_url       TEXT,           -- optional proof photo
  notes           TEXT,
  was_early       BOOLEAN NOT NULL DEFAULT false,
  points_awarded  INT NOT NULL DEFAULT 0
);

-- ─────────────────────────────────────────────
-- NUDGES
-- ─────────────────────────────────────────────
CREATE TABLE nudges (
  id          UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
  task_id     UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES task_instances(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
  from_user   UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES auth.users(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
  to_user     UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES auth.users(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
  message     TEXT,              -- optional custom message, max 120 chars
  sent_at     TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now(),
  CONSTRAINT nudge_rate_limit UNIQUE (task_id, from_user)  -- 1 nudge per person per task
);

-- ─────────────────────────────────────────────
-- NOTIFICATIONS  (in-app)
-- ─────────────────────────────────────────────
CREATE TABLE notifications (
  id          UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
  user_id     UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES auth.users(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
  type        TEXT NOT NULL CHECK (type IN ('nudge', 'reminder', 'assignment', 'completion', 'badge', 'system')),
  title       TEXT NOT NULL,
  body        TEXT,
  data        JSONB,             -- contextual payload (task_id, household_id, etc.)
  is_read     BOOLEAN NOT NULL DEFAULT false,
  created_at  TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now()
);

CREATE INDEX idx_notifications_user_unread ON notifications(user_id, is_read) WHERE is_read = false;

-- ─────────────────────────────────────────────
-- LEADERBOARD ENTRIES  (monthly snapshots)
-- ─────────────────────────────────────────────
CREATE TABLE leaderboard_entries (
  id              UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
  household_id    UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES households(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
  user_id         UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES auth.users(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
  period_year     INT NOT NULL,   -- e.g. 2026
  period_month    INT NOT NULL,   -- 1–12
  tasks_completed INT NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,
  tasks_early     INT NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,
  streak_weeks    INT NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,
  total_points    INT NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,
  rank            INT,
  badges          TEXT[] DEFAULT '{}',
  UNIQUE (household_id, user_id, period_year, period_month)
);

-- ─────────────────────────────────────────────
-- MEMBER PREFERENCES  (reminder settings)
-- ─────────────────────────────────────────────
CREATE TABLE member_preferences (
  id                    UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
  user_id               UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES auth.users(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
  household_id          UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES households(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
  reminder_hours_before INT[] NOT NULL DEFAULT '{24, 2}',  -- hours before due
  push_enabled          BOOLEAN NOT NULL DEFAULT false,
  email_enabled         BOOLEAN NOT NULL DEFAULT true,
  nudge_enabled         BOOLEAN NOT NULL DEFAULT true,
  updated_at            TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now(),
  UNIQUE (user_id, household_id)
);
```

---

### 5.3 Row-Level Security Policies (Examples)

```sql
-- Users can only see tasks in households they belong to
ALTER TABLE task_instances ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;

CREATE POLICY "Members can view household tasks"
  ON task_instances FOR SELECT
  USING (
    household_id IN (
      SELECT household_id FROM household_members WHERE user_id = auth.uid()
    )
  );

CREATE POLICY "Members can update their own assigned tasks"
  ON task_instances FOR UPDATE
  USING (assigned_to = auth.uid() OR
    household_id IN (
      SELECT household_id FROM household_members
      WHERE user_id = auth.uid() AND role IN ('owner', 'admin')
    )
  );

-- Users only see their own notifications
ALTER TABLE notifications ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;

CREATE POLICY "Own notifications only"
  ON notifications FOR ALL
  USING (user_id = auth.uid());
```

---

### 5.4 Realtime Subscriptions

Enable Realtime on these tables in the Supabase dashboard:

| Table | Events | Use Case |
|---|---|---|
| `task_instances` | `INSERT`, `UPDATE` | Live task board updates |
| `notifications` | `INSERT` | Instant in-app nudges & reminders |
| `leaderboard_entries` | `UPDATE` | Live score updates |

