## 6. Accessibility Standards

TribeTask targets **WCAG 2.1 Level AA** compliance.

### Requirements

| Area | Standard |
|---|---|
| **Color Contrast** | Minimum 4.5:1 for normal text, 3:1 for large text |
| **Keyboard Navigation** | All interactive elements reachable and operable via keyboard |
| **Focus Indicators** | Visible focus ring on all focusable elements (Tailwind `focus-visible:ring`) |
| **ARIA** | Semantic HTML first; ARIA labels on icons, modals, live regions |
| **Screen Reader** | Test with VoiceOver (macOS/iOS) and NVDA (Windows) |
| **Motion** | Respect `prefers-reduced-motion` — disable animations when set |
| **Forms** | All inputs have associated `<label>`, error messages linked via `aria-describedby` |
| **Images** | All `<img>` tags have meaningful `alt` text; decorative images use `alt=""` |
| **Touch Targets** | Minimum 44×44px for all interactive elements (mobile) |
| **Language** | `<html lang="en">` set; use `lang` attribute on mixed-language content |

### Implementation Guidelines

```tsx
// ✅ Correct: Accessible icon button
<button
  aria-label="Mark task as complete"
  className="focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-offset-2 focus-visible:ring-primary"
>
  <CheckIcon aria-hidden="true" />
</button>

// ✅ Correct: Live region for real-time updates
<div aria-live="polite" aria-atomic="true" className="sr-only">
  {latestNotification}
</div>

// ✅ Correct: Form field with error
<label htmlFor="task-title">Task Title</label>
<input
  id="task-title"
  aria-describedby="task-title-error"
  aria-invalid={!!error}
/>
{error && <p id="task-title-error" role="alert">{error}</p>}
```

---

## 7. Engineering Best Practices

### Code Style
- **TypeScript strict mode** enabled (`"strict": true` in `tsconfig.json`).
- **No `any` types** — use generics or `unknown` with type guards.
- **Zod schemas** validate all external input (API, forms, env vars).
- **ESLint** with `eslint-config-next` + `eslint-plugin-jsx-a11y`.
- **Prettier** for consistent formatting (run on save).

### Component Rules
- Components are **pure and composable** — no side effects, no direct DB calls.
- Use **Server Components** for data-fetching; `"use client"` only for interactivity.
- Extract reusable UI to `components/ui/` (Button, Card, Badge, Modal, etc.).
- Follow **atomic design**: atoms → molecules → organisms → pages.

### Performance
- Use **Next.js Image** (`<Image>`) for all images — automatic optimization.
- Prefer **static generation** (`generateStaticParams`) for public pages.
- **Paginate** task lists — never load unbounded datasets.
- Debounce search/filter inputs.

### Security
- **Never expose** Supabase service role key client-side.
- Validate and sanitize all user input server-side (Zod + server actions).
- **RLS enforced** on all tables — never trust client-sent user IDs.
- Use Supabase **Auth helpers** for Next.js (`@supabase/ssr`).
- Rate-limit API routes with middleware (e.g., Upstash Rate Limit).
- `.env.local` never committed — use Vercel environment variables.

### Testing Strategy

| Type | Tool | Coverage Target |
|---|---|---|
| Unit | Vitest | Services, utilities, Zod schemas |
| Component | React Testing Library | All reusable UI components |
| Integration | Vitest + Supabase local | Repository layer, server actions |
| E2E | Playwright | Critical flows (auth, task claim, completion) |

